The paper deals with the study of co-graphs and their subclasses in the directed setting. This involves the analysis of forbidden induced subdigraphs and their characterizations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), which deals with combinatorial structures and their properties. The paper also involves the study of graph theory concepts such as threshold graphs, simple co-graphs, and weakly quasi-threshold graphs, which are covered in sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves the study of graph classes and their relations, which is covered in sub-categories such as cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
